OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FDoddie Weir's sons honour  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffather at memorial         
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The children of Doddie Weir have paid  
OL,6, tribute to their father by reading a   
OL,7, poem about him during an emotional     
OL,8, memorial service in the Borders.       
OL,10,FThe former Scotland rugby international
OL,11,Fdied six years after he was diagnosed  
OL,12,Fwith motor neurone disease (MND).      
OL,14,FHis sons, Hamish, Angus and Ben, wore  
OL,15,Ftartan suits - similar to those worn by
OL,16,Ftheir father - for the service at      
OL,17,FMelrose Parish Church.                 
OL,19,FAnd they recited Requiem for Doddie    
OL,20,F(The Mad Giraffe) by Timmy Douglas.    
